edia.org/wiki/Link_rot\" rel=\"nofollow\">Link rot</a> is evil. <a href=\"http://archive.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Archive</a> <a href=\"http://www.archiveteam.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">everything</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keyboard_shortcut\" rel=\"nofollow\">The keyboard is king</a>. Correctness over performance. Canonicalize, normalize, deduplicate. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself\" rel=\"nofollow\">Don't repeat yourself.</a> <a href=\"http://utf8everywhere.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">UTF-8 > UTF-16.</a> Use <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_typing\" rel=\"nofollow\">static typing</a>: good for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autocomplete\" rel=\"nofollow\">tooling</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IKVM.NET\" rel=\"nofollow\">Re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\" rel=\"nofollow\">use</a>; don't <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_invented_here\" rel=\"nofollow\">re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/reinvent_the_wheel\" rel=\"nofollow\">invent</a>. Correctness, then clarity, then concision and elegance. Play devil's advocate. First understand opponents' positions.</p>\n", "Location":"United States", "DownVotes":"7", "Views":"12", "Reputation":"1534", "DisplayName":"Mechanical snail", "LastAccessDate":"2013-06-02T04:51:14.103"}, "ViewCount":"430", "LastActivityDate":"2012-10-22T03:16:58.013", "Score":"13", "CommentCount":"9", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"75", "DownVotes":"1", "Id":"256", "AccountId":"216182", "Views":"17", "Reputation":"494", "CreationDate":"2011-09-22T18:23:22.447", "DisplayName":"blunders", "LastAccessDate":"2013-03-12T03:28:25.543", "AboutMe":"<p>Ask a question on the new <strong><a href=\"http://linguistics.stackexchange.com\">Linguistics site</a></strong> on Stack Exchange.</p>\n"}}